A high-speed train carrying 225 passengers derails near Santiago de Compostela, Spain, leaving 80 dead and over 140 injured. It is Spain's deadliest rail incident since the 2004 Madrid train bombings, and the country's worst accidental train disaster since the Torre del Bierzo rail disaster in 1944. (Bloomberg) (El Mundo) (Reuters) (BBC)TransAsia Airways Flight 222 crashes into residential buildings in an emergency landing in Taiwan's Penghu Islands, with at least 47 feared dead and 11 injured. (USA Today)